            <title>[FELIX-2421] Implicit bootdelegation doesn&apos;t ignore classloaders if they are inner classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2421</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The implicit (a.k.a., magic) bootdelegation doesn&apos;t bootdelegate if it finds a classloader on the stack which is an inner class of a bundle-loaded class. If the classloader would be loaded from a bundle it will not prevent bootdelegation but if it happens to be an inner class it will. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
